<P>
   EASTERN-DROUGHT (Undated) _ Corn leaves are shriveling into
cigar-like shapes, trout are dying in hot and diminished streams,
and once-green lawns have become patches of yellow as exceptionally
dry weather begins to reach drought proportions in the eastern
United States. By Douglas Martin.
</P>
<P>
   NY-SCHOOL-REPAIR (New York) _ More than 10 years and $9 billion
after the state Legislature established the School Construction
Authority to build and repair New York City schools, it has fallen
far short of the original goal of creating a ``physically fit''
school system by 2000.
</P>
<P>
   PROSTITUTE-KILLERS (Chicago) _ The killings of as many as a
dozen black prostitutes in Chicago over the last four years are the
work of four killers, the police have concluded and have issued a
citywide warning. A look at the neighborhoods that the killers have
been haunting. By Pam Belluck.
